DIRECTOR - cg.almundo.callcenter.model.EmployeeType
Director Type, level 3 of attention
dispatchACall() - Method in class cg.almundo.callcenter.CallCenterTest
it tests the CallCenter process a call, and check it found attention
dispatchCall() - Method in class cg.almundo.callcenter.Dispatcher
Method which process a call first the queue of calls is checked then it looks for an employee ready to take the call, it is executed by the stream bellow, it orders the list of employees by EmployeeType, setting Operators, Supervisor and Director, in order so, it filters the free employees and get first available if an employee was found the employee is call to attend(respond) the call
Dispatcher - Class in cg.almundo.callcenter
Dispatcher is the class responsible to manage the list of Employee and receive Calls it manages the incoming calls, save it for attention in a Queue, keep them to process according to the employees availability it assigns a call to an employee to respond it
Dispatcher(List<Employee>) - Constructor for class cg.almundo.callcenter.Dispatcher
The dispatcher is created with the list of employees to manage
dispatchTenCalls() - Method in class cg.almundo.callcenter.CallCenterTest
It tests the CallCenter process ten calls in line, check if the last one was ok
dispatchTenConcurrentCalls() - Method in class cg.almundo.callcenter.CallCenterTest
It tests ten concurrent calls, it creates a services executor to call the dispatcher at the same time for the ten calls
dispatchTwentyConcurrentCalls() - Method in class cg.almundo.callcenter.CallCenterTest
It tests more than ten concurrent calls, it creates a services executor to call the dispatcher at the same time for twenty calls
